sentences: Ani Kavafian (Armenian: Անի Գավաֆեան, born May 10, 1948, Istanbul) is a classical violinist and professor at the Yale School of Music.
After immigrating to the United States in 1956, she began violin studies in Detroit, Michigan with Ara Zerounian and then with Mischa Mischakoff.
In 1973, she was a winner of the Young Concert Artists International Auditions, where she now serves as president of their Alumni Association.
In 1973, she was a winner of the Young Concert Artists International Auditions, where she now serves as president of their Alumni Association.
In 1979, she was the recipient of the Avery Fisher Career Grant.
The same year, she became a member of the Chamber Music Society of Lincoln Center; she continues to tour the United States, Canada and Europe with CMS.
Over the years, Ani has taught at the Mannes School of Music and the Manhattan School of Music, Queens College, McGill University, and Stony Brook University.
She was appointed as a full professor in the Practice of Violin at Yale University in 2006.
Her instrument is the 1736 “Muir-McKenzie” Stradivarius.
